\par }{\b\f39\insrsid2255033 1.1 October 18, 2002 }{\f4\insrsid2255033 
\par  
\par  This version introduces the ability to connect to any MUX, among many other things (see below). 
\par  
\par  }{\i\f38\insrsid2255033 Players}{\f4\insrsid2255033 : If Thud appears to 'lag' 
your connection and commands you put in are not sent to the game after a short period of time, the cause is the administrators not increasing the command_quota_increment. Talk to them, it's not my fault. =) 
\par  
\par  }{\i\f38\insrsid2255033 BTech MUX Admins}{\f4\insrsid2255033 : In order for Thud to work on your site, you need to satisfy 2 requirements:
\par    1. The HUDINFO protocol must be implemented
\par    2. The command_quota_increment must be increased. Use: @admin command_quota_increment=4
\par 
\par  Due to changes in the preferences file format, your preferences will be reset on starting this version. Sorry. Again.  
\par 
\par  }{\i\f38\insrsid2255033 New Features / Other Changes:}{\f4\insrsid2255033 
\par  
\par   * Thud can now display this list of changes in a dialog box. It's in the File menu.
\par   * A preference to adjust the length of heading/speed indicator lines on contacts on the map. The lower the number, the longer the line.
\par   * A preference to limit the amount of lines in the scrollback. Keeping this number lower reduces memory usage and speeds up Thud.
\par   * A new menu with 3 menu items to control the speed of updates that Thud sends. Keep it on Slow to reduce bandwidth usage, crank it to Fast when bad guys show up.
\par   * Thud now has an option to keep 'old' data instead of overwriting it with 'unknown.' If it 'Erase Unknown Terrain' is set, Thud will overwrite any old terrai
n and turn it to a black hex if it gets a '?' for it now. This mostly happens underground. If you want to keep a 'backlog' of terrain underground, uncheck this option.
\par   * Thud keeps 'expired' contacts around 3 times longer now. 
\par   * Thud no longer colors destroyed contacts grey, leaving that color soley for expired contacts. In addition, enemy destroyed contacts will not be displayed in bold any longer. Destroyed contacts are still styled strike-through however.
\par   
\par  }{\i\f38\insrsid2255033 Bug fixes:}{\f4\insrsid2255033 
\par  
\par   * Finally found and fixed the 'straight lines aren't straight' bug. Hexes are properly shaped now.
\par   * Reduced memory usage of map data
\par   * Increased efficiency of parsing data from the MUX
\par   * Thud won't keep sending commands if it's lagged... it'll hold up until it gets some data again before resuming spamming you
\par   * Tabs are closer to the right size in the main window
\par   
\par }{\b\f39\insrsid2255033 1.0 September 16, 2002}{\f4\insrsid2255033 
\par 
\par  The focus of the final 1.0 release has been enhancements in speed and bug fixes. There are also a few minor new features.
\par  All users are encouraged to use this new release and upgrade from any older version.
\par  Note: Due to changes in the preferences file format, your preferences will be reset on starting this version. Sorry.
\par  
\par  }{\i\f38\insrsid2255033 New Features:}{\f4\insrsid2255033 
\par  
\par   * Better ANSI support: background colors and underline mode now supported
\par   * If you are in a tank, it will show a red line indicating turret facing
\par   * Other jumping mechs show a green line indicating jump heading
\par   * Hex numbers along side and top now have a black bar behind them to make them much easier to read
\par   * Hex numbers display at any zoom level - they skip numbers at far out zoom to make them readable
\par   * New option to display your heat level in the tactical display underneath your unit
\par   
\par  }{\i\f38\insrsid2255033 Bug Fixes:}{\f4\insrsid2255033 
\par  
\par   * Much much quicker connect-to-MUX time
\par   * Much quicker text handling
\par   * More efficient and usable map scrolling
\par   * Contact window listing is quicker and flickers less
\par   * Elevation numbers now show when 'Darken Elevations' is turned off
\par   * If the connection is dropped for some reason, Thud should now behave better. Choose your connection from the menu to reconnect
\par   * Menu items properly disabled/enabled depending on connection status
\par   * Choosing a new connection while still connected should disconnect properly first, then reconnect
\par   * No more duplicate contacts on unknowns (seismic or BAP contacts)
\par   * More misc. bug fixes than you can shake a stick at
\par 
